#Creating New Variables
Data1$host <- ifelse(Data1$host_taxid==9606, "Human", 
                             ifelse(Data1$host_taxid==9615, "Dog", 
                                    ifelse(Data1$host_taxid==9685, "Cat", NA)))

Data1$bodysite_num <- ifelse(Data1$BodySite =="Nose", 1, 
                             ifelse(Data1$BodySite=="Mouth", 2, 
                                    ifelse(Data1$BodySite=="Inguinal", 3, 
                                           ifelse(Data1$BodySite=="Lesion", 4, NA))))
Data1$homearea_num <- ifelse(Data1$homearea=="rural (agricultural)", 1, 
                             ifelse(Data1$homearea=="rural (non-agricultural)", 2, 
                                    ifelse(Data1$homearea=="suburban", 3, 
                                           ifelse(Data1$homearea=="urban", 4, NA))))
Data1$urban1 <- ifelse(Data1$homearea=="rural (agricultural)", 0, 
                             ifelse(Data1$homearea=="rural (non-agricultural)", 0, 
                                    ifelse(Data1$homearea=="urban", 1,
                                           ifelse(Data1$zip==19064, 1,
                                                  ifelse(Data1$zip==8022, 1,
                                                         ifelse(Data1$zip==17057, 1,
                                                                ifelse(Data1$zip==17109, 1,
                                                                       ifelse(Data1$zip==17078, 0,
                                                                              ifelse(Data1$zip==17022, 0,
                                                                                     ifelse(Data1$zip==8330, 0, NA))))))))))
Data1$petloc_num <- ifelse(Data1$petloc =="indoor", 1, 
                            ifelse(Data1$petloc=="indoor and outdoor", 2, 
                                   ifelse(Data1$petloc=="outdoor", 3, NA)))
Data1$urban_name<- ifelse(Data1$urban1==1, "urban", "rural")
Data1$host_site <- ifelse(Data1$host =="Human" & Data1$BodySite =="Nose", "1. Human Nares", 
                           ifelse(Data1$host =="Human" & Data1$BodySite =="Inguinal", "2. Human Inguinal", 
                                  ifelse(Data1$host =="Human" & Data1$BodySite =="Lesion", "Human Lesion",
                                         ifelse(Data1$host =="Dog" & Data1$BodySite =="Nose", "3. Dog Nares", 
                                                ifelse(Data1$host =="Dog" & Data1$BodySite =="Mouth", "4. Dog Oral", 
                                                       ifelse(Data1$host =="Cat" & Data1$BodySite =="Nose", "5. Cat Nares",
                                                              ifelse(Data1$host =="Cat" & Data1$BodySite =="Mouth", "6. Cat Oral", NA)))))))
Data1$host_site_num <- ifelse(Data1$host =="Human" & Data1$BodySite =="Nose", 1, 
                          ifelse(Data1$host =="Human" & Data1$BodySite =="Inguinal", 2, 
                                 ifelse(Data1$host =="Human" & Data1$BodySite =="Lesion", 0,
                                        ifelse(Data1$host =="Dog" & Data1$BodySite =="Nose", 3, 
                                               ifelse(Data1$host =="Dog" & Data1$BodySite =="Mouth", 4, 
                                                      ifelse(Data1$host =="Cat" & Data1$BodySite =="Nose", 5,
                                                             ifelse(Data1$host =="Cat" & Data1$BodySite =="Mouth", 6, NA)))))))
Data1$host_site_comb <- ifelse(Data1$host =="Human" & Data1$BodySite =="Nose", "1. Human Nares", 
                          ifelse(Data1$host =="Human" & Data1$BodySite =="Inguinal", "2. Human Inguinal", 
                                 ifelse(Data1$host =="Human" & Data1$BodySite =="Lesion", "Human Lesion",
                                        ifelse(Data1$host =="Dog" & Data1$BodySite =="Nose", "3. Animal Nares", 
                                               ifelse(Data1$host =="Dog" & Data1$BodySite =="Mouth", "4. Animal Oral", 
                                                      ifelse(Data1$host =="Cat" & Data1$BodySite =="Nose", "3. Animal Nares",
                                                             ifelse(Data1$host =="Cat" & Data1$BodySite =="Mouth", "4. Animal Oral", NA)))))))
#Create Filtered Datasets
Human <- filter(Data1, host_taxid==9606)
DogCat <- filter(Data1, !host_taxid==9606)  #two different ways to subset data logical operators
DogCat <- filter(Data1, host_taxid==9615 | host_taxid==9685)
Dog <- filter(Data1, host_taxid==9615)
Cat <- filter(Data1, host_taxid==9685)
Data_nolesions <- filter(Data1, !BodySite=="Lesion")

shannon_plot<-ggplot(Data_nolesions, aes(x=urban_name, y=shannon)) + 
  geom_boxplot(outlier.color=NA, width=0.4, notch=FALSE) +
  geom_point(aes(color=petnumber))
shannon_plot_color <- shannon_plot + scale_colour_gradient(low = "#56B1F7", high = "#132B43") + labs(color="Number of Pets\nin House")
shannon_plot_color+facet_wrap(~ host_site, ncol=2) + theme(            ##facet_wrap for one variable, can do nrow or ncol
  strip.text.y = element_text(size=14, face="bold"),

  ggtitle("Shannon Diversity") + theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
